snippet.textDisplay:
I look forward to how this team plays when they have Nurkic, Whiteside, Collins, and Labissiere to protect the paint. Trevor Ariza coming in to start at SF for the rest of this season should be interesting to see. I truly believe the blazers will at least make the second round of the playoffs this years. Then next season, they'll have the team the envisioned.


PG: Dame/Simons/CJ
SG: CJ/*Trent Jr*
SF: Rodney Hood/Melo/Ariza
PF: Collins/Labissere
C: Nurkic/Whiteside


There's no telling if Melo and Ariza will resign, but really hope Melo takes the humble and loyal route to stick with Portland for another season or two. I like his energy and his game.
